00:26:47,190 --> 00:26:48,315
What is this wine?

483
00:26:48,399 --> 00:26:50,025
- It's delicious.
- It's great.

484
00:26:51,486 --> 00:26:53,862
(clears throat) Was that your fiancé?

485
00:26:53,946 --> 00:26:56,698
Uh, yes, yes.

486
00:26:56,783 --> 00:26:59,451
Why were you so nervous,
speaking to him?

487
00:26:59,535 --> 00:27:01,328
What, was I nervous?

488
00:27:01,412 --> 00:27:03,580
Yes. You turned red.

489
00:27:03,664 --> 00:27:05,165
Well...

490
00:27:05,249 --> 00:27:07,417
Well, I'm sure it's the wine.

491
00:27:07,502 --> 00:27:10,253
Would he be upset if he knew
we were dining together?

492
00:27:10,338 --> 00:27:12,088
No, not at all.
Are you kidding?

493
00:27:13,132 --> 00:27:17,636
I mean, I don't think he'd love
the basic concept of me

494
00:27:17,720 --> 00:27:21,181
sitting with a man,
drinking wine over candlelight,

495
00:27:21,265 --> 00:27:24,768
but he'd quickly realize
there'd be nothing to worry about, so...

496
00:27:25,895 --> 00:27:29,481
Would you ever withhold your work
from the public out of rage?

497
00:27:29,565 --> 00:27:31,650
No, no, no, not like my father.

498
00:27:31,734 --> 00:27:33,318
Oh no, I told you...

499
00:27:33,402 --> 00:27:36,154
I affirm life despite everything.

500
00:27:37,657 --> 00:27:38,907
Right, right.

501
00:27:38,991 --> 00:27:44,120
Well... I'd be curious
to see your work.

502
00:27:45,122 --> 00:27:46,164
Really?

503
00:27:47,291 --> 00:27:51,002
Why? I mean,
you are so disapproving of me.

504
00:27:51,087 --> 00:27:53,380
Well, I've gotten to know you better,

505
00:27:53,464 --> 00:27:56,758
and, you know, it'd be interesting,

506
00:27:56,843 --> 00:28:00,053
and, after all, you are a Catalan painter,
and that's my subject.

507
00:28:00,137 --> 00:28:02,514
What gave you such an interest
in Catalan culture?

508
00:28:02,598 --> 00:28:08,270
Well, uh... I, uh, fell in love
with Gaudí's church when I was 14,

509
00:28:08,354 --> 00:28:10,188
and one thing led to another.

510
00:28:10,273 --> 00:28:16,528
Hmm. And, uh, you also admire
Spanish guitar, I hear?

511
00:28:16,612 --> 00:28:19,531
Yes, yes. I love the guitar.

512
00:28:19,615 --> 00:28:23,535
Would you like to go to hear
some wonderful guitar tonight?

513
00:28:23,619 --> 00:28:25,078
- Tonight?
- Mm-hmm.

514
00:28:26,122 --> 00:28:29,040
Well, it's a little late,

515
00:28:29,125 --> 00:28:32,586
and, you know,
I'm a little wobbly from the wine.

516
00:28:32,670 --> 00:28:35,922
You said you could hold your alcohol.

517
00:28:36,007 --> 00:28:38,508
Besides, we leave tomorrow.

518
00:28:41,220 --> 00:28:42,429
Okay, sure.

519
00:28:42,513 --> 00:28:43,680
Great.

520
00:28:46,058 --> 00:28:49,060
(playing "Granada")

521
00:29:41,739 --> 00:29:44,074
That was, uh...
that was unbelievable.

522
00:29:44,158 --> 00:29:45,492
Thank you. Thank you.

523
00:29:45,576 --> 00:29:48,995
I was looking at your face,
and you looked very moved.

524
00:29:49,080 --> 00:29:50,080
Yes, yes.

525
00:29:50,164 --> 00:29:52,165
A few times I saw a look like that.

526
00:29:52,249 --> 00:29:54,918
Right, and on Maria Elena, I'm sure.

527
00:29:55,002 --> 00:29:56,795
Well, yes, maybe on Maria Elena,

528
00:29:56,879 --> 00:30:01,007
when she saw or heard
something that moved her, yes.

529
00:30:01,092 --> 00:30:02,926
You...

530
00:30:03,010 --> 00:30:04,928
You're still in love with her.

531
00:30:06,347 --> 00:30:08,640
No, I'm not. I'm not.

532
00:30:08,724 --> 00:30:10,934
Mmm, that confirms it.

533
00:30:11,018 --> 00:30:13,561
No, she will always
be a part of me,

534
00:30:13,646 --> 00:30:16,398
and she's
an important person in my life,

535
00:30:16,482 --> 00:30:21,069
but for the two of us,
something was not working.

536
00:30:22,238 --> 00:30:24,030
What element?

537
00:30:24,115 --> 00:30:25,949
We never found out.

538
00:30:30,287 --> 00:30:31,371
(mumbles)

539
00:30:32,790 --> 00:30:36,626
You said you were looking at my face.

540
00:30:37,837 --> 00:30:38,920
Why?

541
00:30:39,005 --> 00:30:41,047
Why were you looking at mine?

542
00:30:41,132 --> 00:30:42,382
Was I?

543
00:30:42,466 --> 00:30:44,509
You probably saw my tears.

544
00:30:44,593 --> 00:30:45,635
Yes.

545
00:30:46,637 --> 00:30:47,971
Yeah, um...

546
00:30:48,055 --> 00:30:50,015
I'm a little out of control.

547
00:30:50,099 --> 00:30:53,685
I was looking at your face
because I find it very beautiful.

548
00:30:53,769 --> 00:30:55,103
You do?

549
00:30:55,187 --> 00:30:56,646
Of course I do.

550
00:30:58,107 --> 00:31:00,316
Of course I do,
and you know I do.

551
00:31:00,401 --> 00:31:02,402
##

552
00:31:32,433 --> 00:31:34,100
On the trip home, Vicky,

553
00:31:34,185 --> 00:31:37,312
who had mentioned nothing
to Cristina, was silent.

554
00:31:37,396 --> 00:31:39,481
Cristina, on the other hand,
talked nervously.

555
00:31:39,565 --> 00:31:43,610
I must apologize to both of you
for ruining the whole weekend!

556
00:31:43,694 --> 00:31:46,863
I'm completely mortified.
I'm humiliated.

557
00:31:46,947 --> 00:31:49,783
I don't know whether it was the wine...
it could've been the shellfish.

558
00:31:49,867 --> 00:31:51,868
Because, you know,
I have this ulcer,

559
00:31:51,952 --> 00:31:56,164
and I just thank God you knew
enough sights to keep Vicky occupied.

560
00:31:56,248 --> 00:32:00,126
You know, I had these horrible nightmares
that you two would be like oil and water,

561
00:32:00,211 --> 00:32:02,462
hating every minute
of being together.

562
00:32:02,546 --> 00:32:04,547
I just couldn't move.

563
00:32:06,926 --> 00:32:09,594
Vicky buried herself in work
at the library.

564
00:32:09,678 --> 00:32:13,598
She put foolish ideas out of her head
and concentrated on her thesis,

565
00:32:13,682 --> 00:32:16,851
but she found her thoughts
frequently returning to Oviedo.

566
00:32:19,063 --> 00:32:22,065
Cristina, searching for
a means of self-expression,

567
00:32:22,149 --> 00:32:24,234
wandered the streets
of Barcelona,

568
00:32:24,318 --> 00:32:27,278
experimented with
her latest passion, photography,

569
00:32:27,363 --> 00:32:29,697
and believed that she
had made a fool of herself

570
00:32:29,782 --> 00:32:32,158
exactly at the moment of truth
with Juan Antonio.

571
00:32:33,536 --> 00:32:35,203
And then, 48 hours later,

572
00:32:35,287 --> 00:32:37,330
Cristina came to Vicky
with an announcement.

573
00:32:37,414 --> 00:32:38,915
Vicky, he called.

574
00:32:38,999 --> 00:32:40,834
Hmm, what? Who?

575
00:32:40,918 --> 00:32:43,586
Juan Antonio.
He called me just now.

576
00:32:43,671 --> 00:32:45,672
Juan Antonio called you?

577
00:32:45,756 --> 00:32:48,716
Yeah. He wants to see me,
take me to some vineyard,

578
00:32:48,801 --> 00:32:50,343
some wine tasting or something.

579
00:32:50,427 --> 00:32:51,594
I said absolutely.

580
00:32:51,679 --> 00:32:53,471
A wine tasting?

581
00:32:53,556 --> 00:32:56,558
But... what about your ulcer?

582
00:32:56,642 --> 00:32:59,435
Oh, no, no, it's fine.
A little wine's not going to hurt me.

583
00:32:59,520 --> 00:33:01,187
The point is that he wants to see me.

584
00:33:01,272 --> 00:33:02,605
Isn't that great?

585
00:33:02,690 --> 00:33:04,357
- Yeah, yeah.
- I can't believe it!

586
00:33:04,441 --> 00:33:06,109
I never thought he was gonna call.

587
00:33:07,111 --> 00:33:10,029
That's great.
I'm happy for you.

588
00:33:11,949 --> 00:33:14,868
That night, the two women
had trouble falling asleep.

589
00:33:14,952 --> 00:33:17,620
Cristina sat in the kitchen
drinking coffee

590
00:33:17,705 --> 00:33:19,664
and working on her poetry.

591
00:33:19,748 --> 00:33:21,791
##

592
00:33:22,960 --> 00:33:25,295
Vicky, too, was lost
in memories of a night

593
00:33:25,379 --> 00:33:28,089
that now seemed
more and more unreal.

594
00:33:32,428 --> 00:33:35,221
(cell phone rings)

595
00:33:41,604 --> 00:33:42,854
Hello?

596
00:33:42,938 --> 00:33:45,690
Hey, babe.
Did I wake you?

597
00:33:46,442 --> 00:33:47,859
No. No, no, no.

598
00:33:47,943 --> 00:33:50,486
I was just going to sleep.

599
00:33:50,571 --> 00:33:52,280
I'm sorry I called so late.

600
00:33:52,364 --> 00:33:55,366
I had to get out of the office,
get some air and get some coffee,

601
00:33:55,451 --> 00:33:57,160
and I had this great idea.

602
00:33:57,244 --> 00:33:58,745
Check this out.

603
00:33:58,829 --> 00:34:01,497
Dad has contacts
in the American embassy in Spain, right?

604
00:34:01,582 --> 00:34:04,292
I thought I could come early,
work from there on my computer,

605
00:34:04,376 --> 00:34:06,628
and the two of us
could get married in Barcelona.

606
00:34:06,712 --> 00:34:08,254
You said it was a romantic spot.

607
00:34:08,339 --> 00:34:10,423
You know, we'll just do
a quick city hall-type thing.

608
00:34:10,507 --> 00:34:12,091
'Course we'll do it
all over again in New York.

609
00:34:12,176 --> 00:34:14,177
We'll have a huge blowout
for our families and friends,

610
00:34:14,261 --> 00:34:15,845
but I thought it'd be fun.
What do you think?

611
00:34:15,930 --> 00:34:18,723
What... to get married here?

612
00:34:18,807 --> 00:34:19,807
Yeah, why not?

613
00:34:19,892 --> 00:34:21,935
It'd be great to tell our kids
we married in Spain.

614
00:34:22,019 --> 00:34:24,562
Dad's friends would make it
real easy for us.

615
00:34:24,647 --> 00:34:28,608
Oh, I don't know what to say.

616
00:34:30,027 --> 00:34:31,694
You don't sound bowled over.

617
00:34:31,779 --> 00:34:34,364
No, it's, uh...

618
00:34:34,448 --> 00:34:36,699
It's just a surprise.

619
00:34:36,784 --> 00:34:39,410
So? Look, we're gonna marry
in the fall anyway,

620
00:34:39,495 --> 00:34:41,371
and we're gonna
do that too, I promise.

621
00:34:41,455 --> 00:34:43,248
Yeah, so what's the point?

622
00:34:43,332 --> 00:34:45,583
The point is it's different,
it's exciting.

623
00:34:45,668 --> 00:34:47,460
I told the idea to Ken and Alice.

624
00:34:47,544 --> 00:34:49,525
They said they wished
they'd done it...

625
00:34:49,526 --> 00:34:51,506
I mean, you know, in
London in their case...

626
00:34:51,590 --> 00:34:53,091
but they were excited.

627
00:34:53,884 --> 00:34:55,551
Well, I-I...

628
00:34:57,221 --> 00:35:00,014
You sound a bit reluctant.

629
00:35:00,099 --> 00:35:01,891
Me? No.

630
00:35:01,976 --> 00:35:04,560
Why would I... why would I be?

631
00:35:06,063 --> 00:35:07,563
No, I...

632
00:35:09,024 --> 00:35:11,109
I think it's a fine idea.

633
00:35:11,193 --> 00:35:13,569
I think it's great... it's a great idea.

634
00:35:13,654 --> 00:35:16,281
Yeah. Yeah, no, I think
it's gonna be good.

635
00:35:16,365 --> 00:35:18,533
Listen, I'm gonna call you tomorrow.
I know I woke you up.

636
00:35:18,617 --> 00:35:21,869
I'll give you more details tomorrow.
I love you so much.

637
00:35:26,667 --> 00:35:27,875
(beeps off)

638
00:35:27,960 --> 00:35:29,460
("La Ley del Retiro"
by Giulia y Los Tellarini plays)

639
00:35:29,461 --> 00:35:31,587
("La Ley del Retiro"
by Giulia y Los Tellarini plays)

640
00:35:56,739 --> 00:35:59,282
Juan Antonio took Cristina
to a wine tasting.

641
00:36:00,284 --> 00:36:02,076
After, he took her back
to his house,

642
00:36:02,161 --> 00:36:05,204
a lovely place he had purchased
from another painter years ago

643
00:36:05,289 --> 00:36:08,249
and which served
as his home and his studio.

644
00:36:08,334 --> 00:36:10,293
He showed her his work,
which delighted her.

645
00:36:11,337 --> 00:36:13,629
She loved the colors
and the wild, emotional way

646
00:36:13,714 --> 00:36:15,840
he applied the paint
to the canvases.

647
00:36:15,924 --> 00:36:18,968
From there, it was
only one floor up to his bedroom.

648
00:36:19,970 --> 00:36:22,430
He told her of his marriage
to Maria Elena

649
00:36:22,514 --> 00:36:25,600
and their deep love
and their terrible fights.

650
00:36:25,684 --> 00:36:28,353
He told Cristina he had not wanted
to make love with anyone else

651
00:36:28,437 --> 00:36:30,772
in the bedroom they shared till now.

652
00:36:30,856 --> 00:36:33,733
This time, Cristina kept her food down.

653
00:37:25,452 --> 00:37:28,746
Juan took Cristina out
several more times.

654
00:37:28,831 --> 00:37:31,958
They went to see a new sculpture
by a friend of his.

655
00:37:32,042 --> 00:37:34,585
##

656
00:37:34,670 --> 00:37:36,796
He showed her some
of his favorite parts of the city,

657
00:37:36,880 --> 00:37:38,965
where she took photographs.

658
00:37:39,049 --> 00:37:41,259
Juan Antonio was friendly
with all the whores

659
00:37:41,343 --> 00:37:43,511
and thought they would make
wonderful subjects.

660
00:37:51,562 --> 00:37:53,312
He encouraged Cristina's work,

661
00:37:53,397 --> 00:37:56,107
although she was always
too shy to allow him to see it.

662
00:37:57,985 --> 00:37:59,735
He took her to lunch
with his friends,

663
00:37:59,820 --> 00:38:02,363
who were poets and artists
and musicians.

664
00:38:02,448 --> 00:38:04,657
Cristina held her own quite well.

665
00:38:04,741 --> 00:38:07,076
(indistinct conversation)

666
00:38:08,412 --> 00:38:11,289
Meanwhile, one day,
going to study yet again the Park Güell,

667
00:38:11,373 --> 00:38:12,665
which Gaudí had designed

668
00:38:12,749 --> 00:38:15,209
and which figured
quite prominently in her thesis,

669
00:38:15,294 --> 00:38:18,129
Vicky had a chance encounter.

670
00:38:23,010 --> 00:38:25,219
- Vicky.
- Oh, hello.

671
00:38:25,304 --> 00:38:27,346
- I mean, my goodness.
- How are you?

672
00:38:27,431 --> 00:38:28,931
What are you doing here?

673
00:38:29,016 --> 00:38:31,767
Nothing. Just doing some sketches.

674
00:38:31,852 --> 00:38:33,686
Oh, right.

675
00:38:33,770 --> 00:38:37,190
Well, I didn't mean to disturb you, so...

676
00:38:37,274 --> 00:38:39,233
Disturb me, no.
How could you disturb me?

677
00:38:40,235 --> 00:38:43,488
We never had a chance
to say a proper good-bye.

678
00:38:43,572 --> 00:38:46,782
Oh, well, you could've called me.

679
00:38:48,285 --> 00:38:50,244
I... yeah.

680
00:38:50,329 --> 00:38:54,832
I debated it, but I didn't think
there was much point.

681
00:38:54,917 --> 00:38:59,128
Yeah, but you never phoned,
not to say anything...

682
00:38:59,213 --> 00:39:01,255
I mean, "Thank you, it was fun..."

683
00:39:01,340 --> 00:39:04,884
I mean, you don't make love to someone
and then never call them

684
00:39:04,968 --> 00:39:07,136
unless you were greatly disappointed.

685
00:39:07,221 --> 00:39:09,096
Quite the opposite.

686
00:39:09,181 --> 00:39:12,600
But... you have plans to marry,

687
00:39:12,684 --> 00:39:14,560
and I thought it best
to stop anything

688
00:39:14,645 --> 00:39:17,480
before it led to
a bad situation for everyone.

689
00:39:17,564 --> 00:39:19,732
Yeah, well, I'm only saying
that we made love,

690
00:39:19,816 --> 00:39:22,026
and you seemed to drop off
the face of the earth.

691
00:39:22,110 --> 00:39:27,073
I mean, I realize these things
don't mean much to you...

692
00:39:27,157 --> 00:39:30,076
To pursue matters would have
only caused you anxiety,

693
00:39:30,160 --> 00:39:32,453
and for me, a disappointment.

694
00:39:33,497 --> 00:39:37,166
I had the ability to hurt you
after one night?

695
00:39:39,461 --> 00:39:41,420
Maria Elena used to say that...

696
00:39:42,422 --> 00:39:46,300
only unfulfilled love
can be romantic.

697
00:39:48,178 --> 00:39:50,221
Right. Okay.

698
00:39:51,348 --> 00:39:55,226
Well, the truth is,
you're much more suited to Cristina.

699
00:39:56,353 --> 00:39:58,896
I've grown very fond of Cristina.

700
00:40:00,566 --> 00:40:05,444
So, I'm very happy for you
and your husband-to-be.

701
00:40:07,072 --> 00:40:10,199
And I... for you and Cristina.

702
00:40:11,201 --> 00:40:12,201
Right.

703
00:40:13,370 --> 00:40:14,537
- Bye.
- Good-bye.

704
00:40:18,667 --> 00:40:19,834
And so the morning came

705
00:40:19,918 --> 00:40:22,503
when Vicky's husband-to-be
arrived from New York.

706
00:40:22,588 --> 00:40:25,047
("Barcelona" reprises)

707
00:40:31,388 --> 00:40:35,141
Juan Antonio, like certain creative men,
needed always to live with a woman,

708
00:40:35,225 --> 00:40:38,686
and had invited Cristina
to move in with him, which she accepted.

709
00:40:42,482 --> 00:40:44,150
How much do I owe you?

710
00:40:45,569 --> 00:40:48,738
(indistinct greetings)

711
00:40:59,916 --> 00:41:01,917
- So you're with Global Enterprises?
- Yes!

712
00:41:02,002 --> 00:41:03,377
Tom Sutter's an old friend of mine.

713
00:41:03,462 --> 00:41:05,254
Oh, you know Tom Sutter!
We play golf.

714
00:41:05,339 --> 00:41:06,339
- You do?
- Yeah.

715
00:41:06,423 --> 00:41:08,132
I got some stories.
Tom has never beaten me.

716
00:41:08,216 --> 00:41:10,426
Oh, well, he's not
the greatest player in the world...

717
00:41:23,440 --> 00:41:25,358
(sighs)

718
00:41:25,442 --> 00:41:26,901
My God.

719
00:41:27,903 --> 00:41:29,820
You're a whole different person here.

720
00:41:29,905 --> 00:41:31,947
VICKY: What does that mean?

721
00:41:32,032 --> 00:41:34,492
You were so into it.

722
00:41:34,576 --> 00:41:37,203
Well, am I not usually?

723
00:41:37,287 --> 00:41:39,997
(stuttering) Yeah, no, of course you are...

724
00:41:40,082 --> 00:41:42,458
I'm giving you a compliment.

725
00:41:45,504 --> 00:41:47,630
Maybe it's the Barcelona air.

726
00:41:48,799 --> 00:41:50,800
Come here, hold me.
Hold me.

727
00:41:54,554 --> 00:41:56,222
- You okay?
- Yeah.

728
00:41:57,265 --> 00:41:58,265
Yeah.

729
00:41:58,350 --> 00:42:00,518
How's Cristina doing?

730
00:42:00,602 --> 00:42:03,437
Oh, you know, she's already
moved in with some guy.

731
00:42:03,522 --> 00:42:05,564
That was quick.
Don't tell me he's a bullfighter.

732
00:42:05,649 --> 00:42:06,649
No...

