00:56:11,953 --> 00:56:14,579
I thought we could go
for a ride to the countryside later.

979
00:56:14,664 --> 00:56:17,499
I mean, the weather is beautiful.

980
00:56:18,876 --> 00:56:21,336
(speaks Spanish)

981
00:56:21,420 --> 00:56:22,879
In English.

982
00:56:22,964 --> 00:56:24,881
Oh, no, it's fine.

983
00:56:25,925 --> 00:56:27,634
You speak no Spanish?

984
00:56:27,718 --> 00:56:30,554
No. I, uh, studied Chinese.

985
00:56:31,973 --> 00:56:33,223
Chinese?

986
00:56:35,726 --> 00:56:37,227
Why?

987
00:56:37,311 --> 00:56:39,354
I thought it sounded pretty.

988
00:56:40,773 --> 00:56:42,399
Say something in Chinese.

989
00:56:44,193 --> 00:56:45,485
Me?

990
00:56:45,570 --> 00:56:47,654
Mm-hmm.

991
00:56:47,738 --> 00:56:51,575
Um... ni hao ma.

992
00:56:52,868 --> 00:56:54,703
You think that sounds pretty?

993
00:56:56,122 --> 00:56:58,999
Well, maybe not the way
I'm pronouncing it, of course, but...

994
00:56:59,083 --> 00:57:00,292
(chuckles)

995
00:57:05,214 --> 00:57:07,090
Speak English, Maria Elena.

996
00:57:11,596 --> 00:57:13,722
Speak English.

997
00:57:13,806 --> 00:57:15,348
(indistinct; ashtray clanks)

998
00:57:15,433 --> 00:57:18,184
I'm sorry. I'm nervous today.
I had bad dreams.

999
00:57:21,689 --> 00:57:23,189
Would you like to paint?

1000
00:57:23,274 --> 00:57:24,941
Oh, do you paint also?

1001
00:57:26,861 --> 00:57:28,111
Ask him. Ask him.

1002
00:57:28,195 --> 00:57:31,364
He stole everything from me,
his whole style.

1003
00:57:31,449 --> 00:57:33,700
She likes to make up these stories.

1004
00:57:33,784 --> 00:57:36,202
Antonio, your whole way
of seeing is mine.

1005
00:57:36,287 --> 00:57:38,455
JUAN ANTONIO: I'm not saying
that you were not influential.

1006
00:57:38,539 --> 00:57:41,249
- Influential? Influential?
- Yes. Yes, influential.

1007
00:57:41,334 --> 00:57:43,543
But to say that I stole your style...

1008
00:57:43,628 --> 00:57:46,046
To say that I stole your style
is too delusional.

1009
00:57:56,307 --> 00:58:00,143
She always had problems with reality,
and I'm not going to get angry.

1010
00:58:00,227 --> 00:58:01,895
I'm not going to get angry.

1011
00:58:01,979 --> 00:58:03,605
Okay, what did they say
in art school?

1012
00:58:03,689 --> 00:58:05,440
They said I was a genius, right?

1013
00:58:05,524 --> 00:58:07,525
I'm always... I always
encouraged your talent.

1014
00:58:07,610 --> 00:58:11,446
Not talent. I'm not talking about talent.
I said genius. Genius.

1015
00:58:12,490 --> 00:58:14,115
I came close to killing for you.

1016
00:58:14,200 --> 00:58:16,785
Yeah, you came close
to killing me with that chair.

1017
00:58:16,869 --> 00:58:18,745
I was defending myself,

1018
00:58:18,829 --> 00:58:21,331
and you had a razor,
and you were drunk,

1019
00:58:21,415 --> 00:58:23,208
with a razor and raging!

1020
00:58:27,380 --> 00:58:29,255
- JUAN ANTONIO: Never.
- Sí, sí, sí.

1021
00:58:31,676 --> 00:58:33,176
You wanted to kill me for looking?

1022
00:58:36,722 --> 00:58:40,225
I see you with someone else now,
and I'm fine. I'm fine. I'm civil.

1023
00:58:40,309 --> 00:58:41,810
What else do you want?

1024
00:58:41,894 --> 00:58:44,396
##

1025
00:58:56,617 --> 00:58:57,909
As the days passed,

1026
00:58:57,993 --> 00:59:00,912
Cristina observed Maria Elena
and Juan Antonio

1027
00:59:00,996 --> 00:59:03,581
and found the heart
more puzzling than ever.

1028
00:59:14,343 --> 00:59:16,803
Where were you?
Were you working?

1029
00:59:16,887 --> 00:59:19,097
- Yeah, I was trying to.
- Okay.

1030
00:59:19,181 --> 00:59:22,976
I'm so curious, does she really think
that you stole from her?

1031
00:59:23,060 --> 00:59:24,394
Uh...

1032
00:59:25,688 --> 00:59:31,735
Well, um, I guess I took
more from her than I'd like to admit, yes.

1033
00:59:32,737 --> 00:59:36,406
That's why I'm always so sensitive
when she brings it up.

1034
00:59:38,909 --> 00:59:41,161
- I feel kind of sad.
- Why?

1035
00:59:41,245 --> 00:59:43,496
'Cause I feel like
I'm never gonna be able to...

1036
00:59:44,498 --> 00:59:47,667
to influence you
or inspire you in any way.

1037
00:59:47,752 --> 00:59:48,793
No, that's not true.

1038
00:59:48,878 --> 00:59:50,086
That's how I feel.

1039
00:59:50,171 --> 00:59:51,171
That's not true.

1040
00:59:51,255 --> 00:59:52,338
No, that's not true.

1041
00:59:52,423 --> 00:59:55,091
I never heard the Scriab...
the Scriabin?

1042
00:59:55,176 --> 00:59:56,551
- Yeah.
- Piano Sonata?

1043
00:59:56,635 --> 01:00:00,138
Until you played those recordings for me,
and now I can't stop listening to them.

1044
01:00:00,222 --> 01:00:01,556
- No?
- No.

1045
01:00:01,640 --> 01:00:04,559
Well, that... makes me happy.

1046
01:00:05,936 --> 01:00:07,228
CRISTINA: What?

1047
01:00:07,313 --> 01:00:10,815
Maybe it's not a good idea here.

1048
01:00:10,900 --> 01:00:12,150
What?

1049
01:00:12,234 --> 01:00:15,028
I mean, she's been better lately.

1050
01:00:15,112 --> 01:00:18,698
I don't want to... upset her.

1051
01:00:19,742 --> 01:00:21,701
Of course. No. Okay.

1052
01:00:27,917 --> 01:00:30,251
It was at Vicky's afternoon language class,

1053
01:00:30,336 --> 01:00:33,213
which she took several days a week
to improve her Spanish,

1054
01:00:33,297 --> 01:00:35,215
that she met Ben, a young man

1055
01:00:35,299 --> 01:00:38,927
who couldn't stop noticing her
and started to chat her up each day.

1056
01:00:40,054 --> 01:00:42,472
Yeah, I can't believe
they hired me at the consulate,

1057
01:00:42,556 --> 01:00:45,558
because my Spanish
is less than perfect, to say the least.

1058
01:00:45,643 --> 01:00:47,852
No, I think it's good. It's good.

1059
01:00:47,937 --> 01:00:49,187
It's all right.

1060
01:00:49,271 --> 01:00:52,023
Are you enjoying
your time in Barcelona?

1061
01:00:52,107 --> 01:00:54,818
Um, I would if I had more friends.

1062
01:00:54,902 --> 01:00:55,985
Right.

1063
01:00:56,070 --> 01:00:59,280
Yesterday I walked from the beach
up to Park Güell in search of Gaudí.

1064
01:01:00,783 --> 01:01:02,784
Hey, you want to see a movie?

1065
01:01:02,868 --> 01:01:04,410
- A movie?
- Wednesday?

1066
01:01:04,495 --> 01:01:05,829
Afternoon?

1067
01:01:05,913 --> 01:01:06,913
Uh.

1068
01:01:08,249 --> 01:01:09,624
Yeah.

1069
01:01:10,709 --> 01:01:12,377
The movie was a great success,

1070
01:01:12,461 --> 01:01:15,129
and Ben proved to be
very good company for Vicky.

1071
01:01:19,468 --> 01:01:22,095
One afternoon, they ducked
into a store to buy some cherries,

1072
01:01:22,179 --> 01:01:24,597
and when the storekeeper
took a phone call in the back,

1073
01:01:24,682 --> 01:01:26,641
he couldn't resist taking her hand.

1074
01:01:28,060 --> 01:01:29,561
Uh.

1075
01:01:29,645 --> 01:01:31,896
Uh, no, don't.

1076
01:01:31,981 --> 01:01:32,981
No?

1077
01:01:33,983 --> 01:01:35,149
No...

1078
01:01:36,777 --> 01:01:38,987
You do know
that I'm recently married?

1079
01:01:39,071 --> 01:01:40,363
BEN: Yeah.

1080
01:01:40,447 --> 01:01:44,701
I guess I was under the impression
that maybe you jumped into it too quick,

1081
01:01:44,785 --> 01:01:48,663
- maybe you regret it...
- Regr... ha... have I implied that?

1082
01:01:49,665 --> 01:01:51,583
Unless I read into it.

1083
01:01:51,667 --> 01:01:52,834
No, I...

1084
01:01:53,836 --> 01:01:55,670
I shouldn't tell you this. I...

1085
01:01:56,881 --> 01:02:00,425
You know what, I was always someone
who thought I knew exactly what I wanted.

1086
01:02:00,509 --> 01:02:02,385
BEN: But you didn't.

1087
01:02:02,469 --> 01:02:05,013
Well, no, I met somebody else,

1088
01:02:05,097 --> 01:02:09,017
and I'm not gonna get into that story.

1089
01:02:09,101 --> 01:02:10,768
BEN: So, this guy you met...?

1090
01:02:10,853 --> 01:02:14,439
The guy is living with my best friend.

1091
01:02:14,523 --> 01:02:16,608
You know, what am I talking about?

1092
01:02:16,692 --> 01:02:20,862
When I... when I hear myself,
it's just... it's just crazy.

1093
01:02:20,946 --> 01:02:24,782
I just married the guy I wanted.

1094
01:02:24,867 --> 01:02:25,992
BEN: Did you?

1095
01:02:26,076 --> 01:02:27,368
I thought so.

1096
01:02:28,454 --> 01:02:31,039
BEN: So? What happened?

1097
01:02:32,458 --> 01:02:36,210
One goddamn weekend in Oviedo.

1098
01:02:37,212 --> 01:02:39,422
##

1099
01:02:39,506 --> 01:02:44,177
Cristina, Juan Antonio, and Maria Elena
went riding in the country.

1100
01:02:44,261 --> 01:02:47,013
Maria Elena had decided
they would all cook a big dinner together,

1101
01:02:47,097 --> 01:02:49,474
and she insisted
they pick fresh blackberries.

1102
01:02:49,558 --> 01:02:50,725
MARIA ELENA: Wait for me!

1103
01:02:52,561 --> 01:02:54,562
Gives me vertigo!

1104
01:02:56,231 --> 01:02:57,398
(whoos)

1105
01:02:58,192 --> 01:02:59,859
- This is the perfect...
- Here, like that.

1106
01:02:59,944 --> 01:03:00,944
- Okay.
- Like that.

1107
01:03:01,028 --> 01:03:02,320
Can you get some... there.

1108
01:03:02,404 --> 01:03:04,822
- Ow, ow!
- What's wrong? What's...

1109
01:03:04,907 --> 01:03:06,324
What, what, what?

1110
01:03:06,408 --> 01:03:07,533
What happened?

1111
01:03:07,618 --> 01:03:10,495
Wait, no, sit down.
Sit, sit, sit, sit.

1112
01:03:11,914 --> 01:03:14,082
Is it your upper or your lower?

1113
01:03:14,166 --> 01:03:15,625
- Here.
- Here?

1114
01:03:15,709 --> 01:03:17,585
- Yep.
- Hold on, wait.

1115
01:03:18,837 --> 01:03:20,171
- Ow.
- Let me... oh, oh, oh.

1116
01:03:20,255 --> 01:03:21,506
Here, let me...

1117
01:03:25,594 --> 01:03:27,303
- You want some aspirin?
- Yeah.

1118
01:03:27,388 --> 01:03:29,013
I have aspirin in my bag.

1119
01:03:29,098 --> 01:03:30,223
- All right.
- Okay.

1120
01:03:30,307 --> 01:03:32,225
You relax. I'll be right back.

1121
01:03:51,412 --> 01:03:54,288
(Juan Antonio and Maria Elena chatting)

1122
01:03:54,373 --> 01:03:57,417
(Juan Antonio sighing in relief)

1123
01:03:57,501 --> 01:04:00,962
It's all in his head.
He has so much tension.

1124
01:04:01,964 --> 01:04:04,382
To the world,
he's carefree, nothing matters,

1125
01:04:04,466 --> 01:04:06,968
"life is short and with no purpose"
kind of thing,

1126
01:04:07,052 --> 01:04:10,680
but all his fear
just goes to his head.

1127
01:04:10,764 --> 01:04:14,475
(both speaking Spanish)

1128
01:04:16,478 --> 01:04:18,354
You know, she plays piano?

1129
01:04:19,732 --> 01:04:22,483
No, I didn't know.

1130
01:04:22,568 --> 01:04:24,652
Is that why you have
a piano in your house?

1131
01:04:24,737 --> 01:04:26,904
No, I could have been
a concert pianist.

1132
01:04:26,989 --> 01:04:28,239
Yeah, she could have.

1133
01:04:28,323 --> 01:04:30,950
I mean, no one plays
a Scarlatti like Maria Elena.

1134
01:04:31,035 --> 01:04:34,162
She understands Scarlatti,
am I right?

1135
01:04:35,164 --> 01:04:36,789
Do you play music?

1136
01:04:36,874 --> 01:04:42,253
No, I just have to come face-to-face
with the fact that I am not gifted.

1137
01:04:42,337 --> 01:04:46,674
You know, I can appreciate art
and I love music, but...

1138
01:04:46,759 --> 01:04:48,009
It's sad, really,

1139
01:04:48,093 --> 01:04:51,262
because I feel like I have
a lot to express

1140
01:04:51,346 --> 01:04:53,639
and I am not gifted.

1141
01:04:53,724 --> 01:04:55,558
But you do have talent.

1142
01:04:55,642 --> 01:04:57,727
- No.
- Yes.

1143
01:04:57,811 --> 01:04:59,729
What's my talent?

1144
01:04:59,813 --> 01:05:01,814
You take beautiful photographs.

1145
01:05:01,899 --> 01:05:05,151
That's true. She always takes pictures
that she hides from me.

1146
01:05:05,235 --> 01:05:06,527
That's...

1147
01:05:06,612 --> 01:05:08,821
No, that's because they're nothing.

1148
01:05:08,906 --> 01:05:10,823
How do you know I take pictures?

1149
01:05:10,908 --> 01:05:12,909
I found them in your luggage.

1150
01:05:12,993 --> 01:05:15,161
You went through my luggage?

1151
01:05:15,245 --> 01:05:17,163
Of course I went through your luggage!

1152
01:05:17,247 --> 01:05:19,582
First night I was in the house.
I didn't trust you.

1153
01:05:19,666 --> 01:05:22,710
I didn't believe you were
who you said you were.

1154
01:05:22,795 --> 01:05:26,547
I wanted to know who was
really sharing the bed of my ex-husband.

1155
01:05:26,632 --> 01:05:28,341
What?!

1156
01:05:28,425 --> 01:05:29,926
Who knew what I would find there?

1157
01:05:30,010 --> 01:05:32,345
How could I be sure
you were not going to hurt me?

1158
01:05:32,429 --> 01:05:34,806
After all, I had thoughts of killing you.

1159
01:05:34,890 --> 01:05:37,767
##

1160
01:05:42,064 --> 01:05:45,358
So here's a few more.

1161
01:05:46,610 --> 01:05:49,028
Don't say you like them
if you don't like them.

1162
01:05:49,113 --> 01:05:51,656
- What are you talking about?
- They are beautiful!

1163
01:05:51,740 --> 01:05:53,533
- Yeah, you see?
- Look at this!

1164
01:05:54,618 --> 01:05:57,829
The next day, Maria Elena
went out photographing with Cristina.

1165
01:05:57,913 --> 01:06:01,124
She had a superb eye and knew a lot
about the art of photography,

1166
01:06:01,208 --> 01:06:03,126
and taught Cristina
much about the

1167
01:06:03,127 --> 01:06:05,044
aesthetics and subtleties
of picture taking.

1168
01:06:05,129 --> 01:06:07,338
She advised her
to get rid of her digital camera

1169
01:06:07,422 --> 01:06:10,091
and use an old one
for more interesting results.

1170
01:06:10,175 --> 01:06:12,218
She said it was important
to have a darkroom,

1171
01:06:12,302 --> 01:06:14,470
and that she would set one up
in the basement for Cristina

1172
01:06:14,555 --> 01:06:18,015
and teach her various techniques
of developing her own pictures.

1173
01:06:24,481 --> 01:06:25,815
They photographed everything,

1174
01:06:25,899 --> 01:06:28,401
from silly-looking dogs
to grim-faced children...

1175
01:06:29,403 --> 01:06:31,821
but the best subject
was Maria Elena herself.

1176
01:06:59,016 --> 01:07:01,767
Shopping one afternoon,
Vicky and Doug ran into

1177
01:07:01,852 --> 01:07:03,978
Adam Tabachnick and Sally.

1178
01:07:04,062 --> 01:07:07,064
Adam was in the same business
Doug was in and they were friendly,

1179
01:07:07,149 --> 01:07:10,067
although in New York,
they did not spend a lot of time together.

1180
01:07:10,152 --> 01:07:11,861
(laughing) You guys have
gotta be kidding me!

1181
01:07:11,945 --> 01:07:13,279
Hi, it's good to see you!

1182
01:07:13,363 --> 01:07:16,115
Any program on TV,
obviously anything live,

1183
01:07:16,200 --> 01:07:18,492
you can play it back
on your computer.

1184
01:07:18,577 --> 01:07:19,911
So I'm on a flight to Tokyo.

1185
01:07:19,995 --> 01:07:22,121
I'm 40,000 feet up in the air,

1186
01:07:22,206 --> 01:07:25,625
and I am watching the Mets,
live, on my laptop.

1187
01:07:25,709 --> 01:07:27,585
It's amazing.
You're never out of touch.

1188
01:07:27,669 --> 01:07:29,837
We're gonna have the new house
wired for everything.

1189
01:07:29,922 --> 01:07:33,132
I'm looking at those new Japanese
high-definition TV screens.

1190
01:07:33,217 --> 01:07:35,218
You've gotta have my guy
do your installation.

1191
01:07:35,302 --> 01:07:37,845
- He's just a genius with computers and...
- I'll get his card.

1192
01:07:37,930 --> 01:07:40,223
We just did our place in Greenwich.
You have to see it!

1193
01:07:40,307 --> 01:07:43,643
We have this wonderful decorator
you should use.

1194
01:07:43,727 --> 01:07:46,896
He's, um, he's creative,
but he knows when to back off.

1195
01:07:46,980 --> 01:07:50,983
We did it, uh, modern, with just
a splash of antiques here and there.

1196
01:07:51,068 --> 01:07:54,028
I love combining the two,
but God, the prices.

1197
01:07:54,112 --> 01:07:57,281
Do you have any idea
what a good-sized oriental rug costs?

1198
01:07:57,366 --> 01:07:59,158
DOUG: She's right. She's right.

1199
01:07:59,243 --> 01:08:03,454
Actually, there's an old joke.
"100,000 for a Persian rug..."

1200
01:08:03,538 --> 01:08:05,539
##

1201
01:08:16,301 --> 01:08:18,552
Life continued predictably
for Vicky and Doug,

1202
01:08:18,637 --> 01:08:22,306
until one afternoon,
when an unpredictable moment occurred.

1203
01:08:35,529 --> 01:08:38,364
Several days later,
Judy asked Vicky to meet her privately,

1204
01:08:38,448 --> 01:08:40,366
away from the house,
to have coffee.

1205
01:08:41,368 --> 01:08:43,077
What happened the other day...

1206
01:08:44,871 --> 01:08:47,039
- I don't want you to get the wrong idea.
- Oh, no, no, no.

1207
01:08:47,124 --> 01:08:49,084
It's really none
of my business.

1208
01:08:49,085 --> 01:08:51,043
I'm not having an affair
with Mark's partner.

1209
01:08:51,128 --> 01:08:53,045
I'm... I'm not.

1210
01:08:53,130 --> 01:08:55,131
No, I didn't think you were.

1211
01:08:55,215 --> 01:08:58,175
Mm, uh, not that
I haven't had fantasies

1212
01:08:58,260 --> 01:09:03,097
of someone coming along
and taking me out of my situation,

1213
01:09:03,181 --> 01:09:08,102
but the fantasies are not Jay Lewis...

1214
01:09:08,186 --> 01:09:11,147
even though he would like that, he would.

1215
01:09:11,231 --> 01:09:14,734
By "taking you out of your situation"...?

1216
01:09:16,903 --> 01:09:21,866
I haven't... I haven't been in love
with Mark for years.

1217
01:09:21,950 --> 01:09:26,037
I mean, I love him,
but I'm not in love with him.

1218
01:09:27,122 --> 01:09:28,831
I'm sorry to hear that.

1219
01:09:30,208 --> 01:09:32,293
It's funny, I just made...

1220
01:09:33,545 --> 01:09:37,590
I just made the same speech
to my shrink. Huh.

